Project:
                     
                        
                        
                           Repair a Natural Slate Roof
                        
                     
                  


On two occasions I've needed to call Roberts to repair my older slate roof, which sits atop a three story home with a steeply pitched angle.  Frank, at the main office, has consistently been professional, kind, and responsive.

The men who've completed the work have been professional, efficient, and tidy.

Roberts is certainly not a "discount" roofer, so the cost of repairs can initially cause a person to consider second or third opinions.  However, I will NEVER look for those opinions because the cost of the repair and work is fair and deserved.  And so the question of "value for money" ends up being moot when one considers how important the roof of one's home is.



